# Stonefish AUV Simulation - Environment Configuration
#
# Copy this file to .env and update values as needed.
# cp .env.example .env

# X11 Display Configuration
# --------------------------
# These are typically set automatically by your shell.
# Only modify if you have a non-standard X11 setup.

# Display server (usually :0 or :1)
DISPLAY=${DISPLAY:-:0}

# X authority file location
# XAUTHORITY=${HOME}/.Xauthority

# Setup Instructions
# ------------------
# Before running the container, allow local Docker X11 connections:
#
#   xhost +local:docker
#
# To revoke access after you're done:
#
#   xhost -local:docker

# GPU Configuration
# -----------------
# Ensure NVIDIA Container Toolkit is installed:
#   https://docs.nvidia.com/datacenter/cloud-native/container-toolkit/install-guide.html
#
# Verify GPU access:
#   docker run --rm --gpus all nvidia/cuda:11.8-base-ubuntu22.04 nvidia-smi
